This repo has the key scripts for Megan Ding's BCB430 2025-2026 project.

I worked on clustering the isocortex and PFC at different age- and sex-specific levels. I then took the PFC-male-aged vs. PFC-male-adult and PFC-female-aged vs. PFC-female-adult DE genes and analysed them in the context of MDD.

You will have to look at each script, change the output directories, and download the appropriate MDD gene lists, human to mouse homolog, and gmt files to run everything.

The directory structure that I worked with looked like this:

BCB430/
|-scrattch.hicat/
|  |-you will have to clone this repo from https://github.com/AllenInstitute/scrattch.hicat.git
|
|-split_isocortex_data/
|  |-isocortex.h5ad
|  |-isocortex_aged.h5ad
|  ...
|  |-PFC.h5ad
|  |-PFC_female_aged.h5ad
|  ...
|
|-clust_res_hicat/
|  |-labeled/
|  |  |-isocortex.h5ad.rds
|  |  ...
|  |  |-PFC_male_adult.h5ad.rds
|  |
|  |-merged/
|  |  |-isocortex.h5ad.rds
|  |  ...
|  |  |-PFC_male_adult.h5ad.rds
|  |
|  |-isocortex.h5ad.rds
|  ...
|  |-PFC_male_adult.h5ad.rds
|
|-cluster/
|  |-isocortex.h5ad/
|  |  |-DE_results.rds
|  |  |- other plots and enrichment results
|  ...
|  |-PFC_male_adult.h5ad/
|  |  |- other plots and enrichment results
|
|-shell scripts, R scripts, python script
|-gmt, MDD gene list, and human to mouse homolog files  
|-metadata_isocortex.csv

You can probably create a cleaner file structure than me :P

The general steps for my work flow are:

1. python3 subset_isocortexh5ad_pfc_iso.py -> splits isocortex data into non-neuronal, PFC, sex, and age specific subsets into split_isocortex_data/
2. ./run_hicat_cluster.sh (uses hicat_cluster_job.R) -> hicat clusters expression files in split_isocortex_data/ into clust_res_hicat/ , and puts the final merged clusters into clust_res_hicat/merged
-> there is an issue with the heatmap3.R script from the scrattch.hicat package due to R version incompatibility
-> so we work around this by sourcing all the scripts in scrattch.hicat/R and then sourcing new_heatmap3.R to fix the broken function
3. ./run_label_clusters.sh (uses label_clusters.R) -> labels clusters from clust_res_hicat/merged based on metadata_isocortex.csv into clust_res_hicat/labeled
3a. Can run silhouette_scores_hitcat.R in RStudio -> plots go into cluster/
4. ./run_within_cluster_eda_dea.sh (uses within_cluster_eda_dea.R) -> does EDA and DEA on subsets in split_isocortex_data/ based in cell types defined in clust_res_hicat/labeled
5. ./run_btwn_cell_label_dea.sh (uses btwn_cell_label_dea.R) -> does DEA on pairs of subsets defined in the script from split_isocortex_data/ based in cell types defined in clust_res_hicat/labeled
6. ./run_mdd_enrichment.sh (uses mdd_enrichment_btwn_clust.R) -> find overlap of all DE genes within and between all subsets with MDD gene lists and run GO:BP enrichment on the genes in this intersection
6a. Can run gene_set_overlap_heatmap.R in RStudio -> plots go into cluster/
7. ./run_mdd_enrichment_dir.sh (uses mdd_enrichment_btwn_clust_dir.R) -> find overlap of all DE genes within and between all subsets with MDD gene lists and run GO:BP enrichment on the genes in this intersection, stratified by increase and decrease depressive burden
7a. Can run cytoscape_commands.R in RStudio -> you need an instance of Cytoscape running, you will have to use the UI to do any manual adjustments to make the network look nicer
7b. ./run_enrichment_heatmap_sel_cells.sh (uses enrichment_heatmap_sel_cells.R) -> makes top GO:BP term heatmaps for the selected cell types, stratified by increase and decrease depressive burden

